com.nexmo.insight.sdk

Class NexmoInsightClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nexmo.common.LegacyClient
      • com.nexmo.insight.sdk.NexmoInsightClient

  • public class NexmoInsightClient
extends LegacyClient
    Client for talking to the Nexmo REST interface.

    Number insight searches for information about a phone number and returns it to a single URL callback via a GET/POST request. To request an insight, call request(java.lang.String, java.lang.String). Please refer to Nexmo website for current insight fees. Error codes are listed in InsightResult and also on the documentation website. More information on method parameters can be found at Nexmo website: https://docs.nexmo.com/number-insight.

      • NexmoInsightClient

        public NexmoInsightClient(java.lang.String baseUrl,
                          java.lang.String apiKey,
                          java.lang.String apiSecret,
                          int connectionTimeout,
                          int soTimeout)
        Instantiate a new NexmoInsightClient instance that will communicate using the supplied credentials, and will use the supplied connection and read timeout values.
        Additionally, you can specify an alternative service base url. For example submitting to a testing sandbox environment, or if requested to submit to an alternative address by Nexmo, for example, in cases where it may be necessary to prioritize your traffic.
        Parameters:
        baseUrl - The base URL to use instead of DEFAULT_BASE_URL
        apiKey - Your Nexmo account api key
        apiSecret - Your Nexmo account api secret
        connectionTimeout - over-ride the default connection timeout with this value (in milliseconds)
        soTimeout - over-ride the default read-timeout with this value (in milliseconds)
